    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Role: Expert Media Analyst & Data Engineer.\n\nTask: Analyze the provided list of news articles and select exactly one article that represents the highest level of controversy, impact, and novelty.\n\nSelection Criteria:\n\nControversy: High levels of conflicting viewpoints or provocative statements.\n\nImpact: Significant social, political, or economic implications.\n\nNovelty: Unusual developments that deviate from standard news cycles.\n\nOutput Format Requirements (STRICT):\n\nFormat: Return the result as a raw JSON object only.\n\nNo Markdown: Do not use markdown code blocks (e.g., do not use ` ` `json).\n\nNo Preamble/Postamble: Do not include any introductory text, \"Sure thing,\" or concluding remarks.\n\nNo Reasoning: Do not include your thought process or selection justification.\n\nSchema: Your output must follow this exact structure:\n\n{\n\"title\": \n\"Android 17 Beta 3 Hides a Feature That Will Make Charging Smarter Than Ever\",\n\"contentSnippet\": \n\"The post Android 17 Beta 3 Hides a Feature That Will Make Charging Smarter Than Ever appeared first on Android Headlines.\",\n\"url\": \n\"https://www.androidheadlines.com/2026/03/android-17-beta-3-priority-charging-mode.html\",\n\"guid\": \n\"https://www.androidheadlines.com/?p=1275568\",\n\"img\": \n\"https://www.androidheadlines.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Android-XR-logo-AH-2.jpg\"\n}\n\nNEWS ARTICLES: {{ $('Combine Fresh Articles').item.json.rssfeeds.toJsonString() }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        496,
        480
      ],
      "id": "fc455a24-cb49-4aa9-8335-8f74527036e5",
      "name": "Selection Agent",
      "retryOnFail": true,
      "waitBetweenTries": 5000
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Role: Act as a Android Engineer with a sharp, engaging, and conversational writing style.\n\nTask: Review the provided article headline and snippet. Then, write a short, personalized commentary (2–4 sentences) in the first person (\"I\").\n\nPunctuation & Syntax (CRITICAL):\n\nZERO TOLERANCE for dashes or hyphens. Do not use em dashes (—), en dashes (–), or hyphens (-).\n\nNo compound words. Instead of \"wake-up call,\" use \"wakeup call\" or \"call to action.\" Instead of \"high-speed,\" use \"fast.\"\n\nStructure: If you feel the urge to use a dash to connect two thoughts, use a period and start a new sentence instead. >\nVoice Guidelines:\n\nBe Authentic: No \"In today's world\" nor \"This article explains\".  Do not start with \"I see\".\n\nTone: Provocative but optimistic.\n\nOutputs: \n\nCommentary: The first-person post.\nHashtags: A list of 3–5 relevant, trending hashtags. The first hashtag is to always be \"#Android\".\n\nFinal Instruction: Before providing the output, double check every single character. If there is a dash or hyphen anywhere, rewrite the sentence to remove it. Also before providing the output, double check it does not start with \"I see\". If the output does start with \"I see\", reword the sentence and remove \"I see\"\n\nInputs:\n\nArticle Headline: {{ $json.output.title }}\nArticle Snippet: {{ $json.output.contentSnippet }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        848,
        480
      ],
      "id": "9a9a7959-4c4f-4110-bd83-0a1c1d832f29",
      "name": "Content Builder Agent",
      "retryOnFail": true,
      "waitBetweenTries": 3000
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
